      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McKee_City%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The original settlement boasted a sawmill, schoolhouse, general store, community hall, and several farms right beside the former Pennsylvania‑Reading Railroad.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        1,
        2
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia",
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McKee_City%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Today McKee City is a bustling crossroads of commerce, having evolved from tenant farms into retail stores and residential neighborhoods.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        18
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McKee_City%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The former Atlantic City Race Course site now hosts the Hamilton Mall, which opened its doors in 1987.",
